===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} [[gamenian]] 'to play', either via a dialectal survival of {{etyl|enm}} [[gammlen]], a variant of [[gamenen]] 'to play, jest, be merry', or via a derivative of [[gamel]] 'to play games'

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A significant [[risk]], undertaken with a potential gain.
# A risky [[venture]]
#: ''The sailors had taken many '''gambles''' with the sea and always won.

